This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically with diacritic restoration, which is a task related to text processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category. The paper also discusses the advantages of TCN over RNN, which are both commonly used in NLP, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) possible categories as well.
